mprehensive statute exists.<\/p>\r\n<p>The state (government) has the power to severely restrict one's liberty for committing a crime. Therefore, in modern societies, a criminal procedure must be adhered to during the investigation and trial. Only if found guilty, the offender may be sentenced to punishment such as community sentence, imprisonment, life imprisonment or, in some jurisdictions, even death.<\/p>\r\n<p>To be classified as a crime, the act of doing something bad (actus reus) must be usually accompanied by the intention to do something bad (mens rea), with certain exceptions (strict liability).<\/p>\r\n<p>While every crime violates the law, not every violation of the law counts as a crime. Breaches of private law (torts and breaches of contract) are not automatically punished by the state, but can be enforced through civil procedure.<\/p>\r\n<p><\/p>","created_on":"2012-11-28T17:18:53","latitude":null,"geohash":"","short_permalink":"/web/20150108141741/http://www.breakingnews.com\/t\/B","image_credit":"Photo: <a href=\"/web/20150108141741/http://en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Crime\">Wikipedia<\/a>","item_count":49782,"category":"Topic","local_url":"\/topic\/crime-courts\/","kind":"vertical","muted_by_default":false,"links":"","daily_count":130,"livevideo":"","items_resource_uri":"\/api\/v1\/item\/?topics=1","moderation_status":"approved","twitter_username":null,"slug":"crime-courts","related_topics_uri":"\/api\/v1\/topic\/?related_to=1","facebookchat":"","recent_count":18,"latest_item_date":"2015-01-08T14:11:42.155484","wikipedia_url":"/web/20150108141741/http://en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Crime","name":"crime & courts","permalink":"/web/20150108141741/http://www.breakingnews.com\/topic\/crime-courts\/","image_url":"/web/20150108141741/http://upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/4\/4b\/Pierre-Paul_Prud%27hon_-_Justice_and_Divine_Vengeance_Pursuing_Crime.JPG","placetype":"","resource_uri":"\/api\/v1\/topic\/1\/","active":true,"woeid":null},{"id":15,"longitude":